  "interpretation": "At (\u03ba = 0.50, c = 0.50) the committed profiles are behaviorally identical (genome max |\u0394| = 4.2e-07 \u2014 L-BFGS-B endpoint jitter), and the CRN paired difference is +2.5e-05 \u00b1 1.768e-05. The headline results.json residual in this column is therefore pure Monte-Carlo evaluation + restart-selection noise at num_simulations = 1000, giving an honest per-cell payoff noise scale of order tens of payoff units.\n\nAt (\u03ba = 0.90, c = 0.50) the two batches found **structurally different** equilibria (`firefighter(d=0.00) | hero(d=0.00) | hero(d=0.00) | firefighter(d=0.00)` vs `hero(d=0.00) | firefighter(d=0.00) | firefighter(d=0.00) | firefighter(d=0.00)`), and the CRN comparison is decisive: `firefighter(d=0.00) | hero(d=0.00) | hero(d=0.00) | firefighter(d=0.00)` has the higher true team payoff by 9.55 \u00b1 2.73 (t = +3.5). The restart lottery is not just payoff jitter \u2014 it changes *which* equilibrium is reported. Whether the better profile is itself an \u03b5-Nash equilibrium of the shared environment requires the seeded re-solve of issue #445 (best-response search is not re-run here)."
